repo-mirror (0.6.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix variable expansion to handle dependencies correctly
  * Add comprehensive logging for file downloads
  * Fix automatic cleanup to protect files properly
  * Fix file copying from skel to mirror for all file types
  * Add support for translation (i18n) files
  * Improve metadata file pattern matching for modern APT
  * Add support for all modern APT metadata types (dep11, cnf, i18n)
  * Handle optional files gracefully (Release.gpg 404s)
  * Ensure comprehensive coverage of all APT repository features

 -- Debian/Ubuntu Maintainers <debian-apt-mirror@lists.debian.org>  Sun, 24 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000

repo-mirror (0.6.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix size verification for Release files with unknown sizes (size=0)
  * Fix unpacking error in _process_indexes for binaries and sources
  * Fix file_versions.json path resolution and directory creation
  * Improve error handling for files with unknown sizes

 -- Debian/Ubuntu Maintainers <debian-apt-mirror@lists.debian.org>  Sun, 24 Nov 2024 00:00:00 +0000

repo-mirror (0.6.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rename package from apt-mirror to repo-mirror to avoid conflicts with
    existing apt-mirror package in Debian/Ubuntu repositories
  * Tool name remains 'apt-mirror' as a drop-in replacement for the Perl version

 -- Debian/Ubuntu Maintainers <debian-apt-mirror@lists.debian.org>  Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000

repo-mirror (0.6.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Rewrite in Python with async support
  * Add diff serving capability using xdelta3
  * Improve error handling and progress reporting
  * Add automatic retry with exponential backoff
  * Add resume partial downloads support
  * Add checksum verification option
  * Backward compatible with existing mirror.list configuration
  * All dependencies available in Debian/Ubuntu repositories

 -- Debian/Ubuntu Maintainers <debian-apt-mirror@lists.debian.org>  Mon, 01 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000

